---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---
<PageLayout title="About Us - Online Ruler">
  <h1 class="text-[32px] md:text-[40px] font-semibold tracking-tight-apple mb-6">About Us</h1>
  
  <p>Welcome to <strong>Online Ruler</strong>, the most precise and user-friendly digital measuring tool on the web.</p>

  <h2 class="text-[20px] font-semibold tracking-tight-apple mt-6 mb-2">Our Mission</h2>
  <p>Our mission is simple: to provide a reliable, universally accessible, and highly accurate online ruler for everyone. Whether you are a student, a designer, an engineer, or just someone who needs a quick measurement without digging through drawers for a physical ruler, we are here to help.</p>

  <h2 class="text-[20px] font-semibold tracking-tight-apple mt-6 mb-2">Why We Built This</h2>
  <p>We noticed that many existing online rulers were either inaccurate, cluttered with ads, or lacked proper calibration tools for modern high-DPI displays. We set out to build a tool that uses intelligent screen-size detection, alongside foolproof manual calibration methods (like the Credit Card method), ensuring that 1 inch on your screen is exactly 1 inch in real life.</p>

  <h2 class="text-[20px] font-semibold tracking-tight-apple mt-6 mb-2">Our Technology</h2>
  <p>Built with modern web technologies, our application runs entirely in your browser. This means no downloads, no app installations, and complete privacy. We continuously update our device database to support the latest smartphones, tablets, and monitors, ensuring our auto-calibration remains the best in the industry.</p>

  <p class="mt-8">Thank you for using Online Ruler. Measure twice, cut once!</p>
</PageLayout>
